ut their Hawking masses remain\nidentical, implying that the event horizon obeys the same energy-flux balance\nlaw as the apparent horizon. At least in the case of a binary system, the\ndifference between their surface areas remains extremely small even in the late\nstages of inspiral. In the course of our analysis, we also numerically\nillustrate puzzling behaviour in the black hole's motion around the binary's\ncenter of mass.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Sep 2021 12:59:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 7 Dec 2021 01:16:16 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 8 Jan 2022 22:22:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-24"}
