tion within shocked gas near the\nstagnation point. X-ray flares seen in $\\eta$ Carinae have not occurred in WR\n140, suggesting the absence of large-scale wind inhomogeneities. Relatively\nconstant soft emission revealed during the X-ray minimum is probably not from\nrecombining plasma entrained in outflowing shocked gas.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Sep 2021 13:59:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-05"}
